# SECTION 9: GIT LFS - LIBRARIES AND EXECUTABLES
# =========================================================================
# Compiled libraries
*.dll                   lfs
*.pdb                   lfs
*.so                    lfs
*.dylib                 lfs
*.a                     lfs
*.lib                   lfs
# Note: *.framework is a directory bundle on macOS, not a single file.
# Binary contents inside (.dylib, executables) are handled by patterns above.
# If you need to track vendored frameworks, handle their internal binaries.
# Executables and build outputs
*.apk                   lfs
*.exe                   lfs
# iOS/visionOS specific
*.car                   lfs
# =========================================================================
# SECTION 9a: XCODE ASSET CATALOGS (.xcassets)
# =========================================================================
# NOTE: .xcassets is a directory (package), not a single file.
# We handle the contents individually for proper tracking.
# Asset catalog JSON metadata (text, should be diffable)
# This pattern matches all Contents.json files including those in xcassets
**/Contents.json                    text linguist-language=json
# Asset catalog binary contents use LFS via the image rules above
# (*.png, *.jpg, *.pdf, etc. are already configured for LFS)
# =========================================================================
# SECTION 10: GIT LFS - FONTS
# =========================================================================
*.otf                   lfs
*.ttf                   lfs
